Southern Miss won 32-10. (Eli Baylis/The Hattiesburg ... more Photo: Eli Baylis, MBO / Associated Press UTSA falls to Southern Mississippi 1 / 1 Back to Gallery An aggressive Southern Miss defense held UTSA scoreless for a little more than a half Saturday and then rolled to a 32-10 victory in a Conference USA West Division game.
Southern Miss (4-3, 2-1) set the tone early, sacking UTSA quarterback Dalton Sturm three times in the first quarter of a homecoming game played at Roberts Stadium in Hattiesburg, Mississippi.
